ActInternational Convention for the Conservation of Atlantic Tunas and Order in Council P.C. 1968-1197 of June 28, 1968
PrecisAppointment of JAMES DOUGLAS FRASER of Huntley, Prince Edward Island, as a Canadian Commissioner to the International Commission for the Conservation of Atlantic Tunas, to hold office during pleasure for a term of two years, effective August 1, 2009, in the place of Gerald J. Chidley.
